From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matt Roper <matthew.d.roper@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Oct 2025 13:09:52 -0700
Subject: drm/xe: Skip L2 / TDF cache flushes if primary GT is disabled

If the primary GT is disabled via configfs, GT-side L2 and TD cache
flushes are unnecessary since nothing is using/filling these caches.

Reviewed-by: Tejas Upadhyay <tejas.upadhyay@intel.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20251013200944.2499947-34-matthew.d.roper@intel.com
Signed-off-by: Matt Roper <matthew.d.roper@intel.com>
(backported from commit 082547d8b401f8eef076d18344c267fe1bddb055 linux-next)
Signed-off-by: Bommu Krishnaiah <krishnaiah.bommu@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c
index 51a603460..da4ae4392 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_device.c
@@ -1038,6 +1038,8 @@ void xe_device_l2_flush(struct xe_device *xe)
 	unsigned int fw_ref;
 
 	gt = xe_root_mmio_gt(xe);
+	if (!gt)
+		return;
 
 	if (!XE_WA(gt, 16023588340))
 		return;
@@ -1083,6 +1085,9 @@ void xe_device_td_flush(struct xe_device *xe)
 		return;
 
 	root_gt = xe_root_mmio_gt(xe);
+	if (!root_gt)
+		return;
+
 	if (XE_WA(root_gt, 16023588340)) {
 		/* A transient flush is not sufficient: flush the L2 */
 		xe_device_l2_flush(xe);
-- 
2.43.0

